The SS192 "Green Ammo" is the predecessor to the current SS195LF which uses the same 27gr HP aluminum core bullet but with a lead free primer, hence the LF designation. The SS192 “green ammo” or environmentally friendly ammo was SS195LF ammo before they changed the name and box. The manufacture (FN Herstal) relates the labeling as a way to visibly mark the packaging so that there is a lower chance for this to be mixed up with SS192 ammunition that contains lead primer.

title: For Sale:  6.5 Swedish Mauser Ammo - Military M41 Tracer & Ball
postcontent:
Here is 120 total rounds of real Swedish military manufactured ammo. You just don't see this much anymore which is a shame since it's some of the very best ammo you can feed your old Swedish Mausers or your AG42b.

Both the tracer and the ball ammo in this auction carry the M41 designation which means it was produced for their M41b sniper rifle. So it's of highest quality and it's very accurate. It's also none corrosive. 

There are two 20 round boxes of FMJ ball ammo which is brass case with a 139 grain FMJ bullet. This ammo is 1987 manufacture and it's exceptionally clean with bright shiny brass cases.

Then there are three 20 round boxes of the same thing except it is the M41 long range red tracer variety with white painted bullet tips. The tracer compound ignites about 100 meters down range and continues for another 800 meters or more. In other words it traces for a long way. It's brass case and there is some tarnish showing, but nothing that will affect it's function. I shot a bunch of this ammo and 100% of the tracers ignited.

Finally there is one 20 round box of brass case ammo with red wooden bullets. This ammo was intended to be BLANK ammo and functions as such with a special blank firing adapter that screws on to the muzzle of Swedish Mausers. This adapter is meant to shred the wooden bullet, however this ammo would be dangerous if not lethal at close range without the adapter. So you must treat this as you would with any other real live ammo.

Asking $130 for the lot with pickup in the Brandon area. Buyer must be at least 18 years old. I can ship this ammo via UPS ground at the buyers expense. 

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Savage 116 Stainless/Accutrigger/bedded stock/Scope-Sunshade/Gator Skin Paint
postcontent:
Up for sale is a beautiful Savage  Model 116 Long Action.  It's completely stainless including the trigger guard, magazine well and magazine and 22" barrel.  It makes for a great hunting rifle as you don't have to worry about beating the synthetic stock up or the barrel rusting on those wet rainy days in the tree stand.   The fore end has been aluminum pillar bedded for precision accuracy when shooting off of a bipod or any position that increases upward pressure on the fore end of the stock on the free floated barrel. 

The bolt and trigger have also had the tooling marks polished off, the action feels sweet-WAY BETTER THAN ANY SAVAGE AXIS!! The bolt pull is probably the smoothest I've ever felt on a savage. The accutrigger is crisp and smooth as well.  Was measured at a little over 2.3 pounds of break. 

As stated earlier it is based on the long action receiver meaning all it takes is a new barrel to re-chamber to .300 win mag/.338 Federal/.338WM..etc.-remove the barrel nut, install the new barrel, head-space the new barrel and viola! 

The synthetic stock and scope have been painted and cured in a gator skin theme that really looks great, definitely one of a kind. 

It is coupled with a Bushnell 3-9x40 with a sun shade and butler creek flip ups siting on a stainless scope base. 

It was over $700 new with taxes. The first $550 takes it home.  Less than 30 shots though the new setup.  No I don't want your beat up 870's, 500's etc..

Pictures don't do it justice, it is really a head turner in person.
